100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 27, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing the ongoing tensions in the Far East, particularly regarding Japan's expansionist policies. In Britain, the government faced criticism over its handling of the coal miners' strike, drawing attention to the growing labor unrest. Meanwhile, the United States continued to grapple with Prohibition, as illegal speakeasies thrived in major cities.
